The paper deals with graph differentiation in first order logic, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic (cs.LO). The use of the Weisfeiler-Leman algorithm and the analysis of its iterations suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The focus on graphs and their properties makes the paper relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of a game between two players and the decoupling of causal dependencies suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the analysis of color classes and their size suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of computational geometry (cs.CG).
